## Summary
- stop refreshing chat history immediately after a displayable chat final event
- update the TUI event-handler tests to cover the stale-history overwrite case and current optimistic run binding behavior

## Why
A displayable final response is already rendered from the live event stream. Immediately reloading chat history can race with transcript persistence and replace the just-rendered final response with stale history, making the TUI appear one response behind until the next user message.

## Real behavior proof
- **Behavior or issue addressed:** The macOS TUI could show a final response briefly, then lose it after an immediate stale history refresh, making the latest assistant response appear one turn behind until the next user message.
- **Real environment tested:** Real installed OpenClaw TUI on Nao's macOS machine, `OpenClaw 2026.5.22 (a374c3a)`, Node `v24.15.0`, installed under `/Users/naokitange/.nvm/versions/node/v24.15.0/lib/node_modules/openclaw`.
- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Applied the equivalent one-line patch to the installed TUI bundle, then inspected the live installed bundle over SSH to verify the displayable final branch no longer calls `maybeRefreshHistoryForRun(evt.runId)` before `chatLog.finalizeAssistant(finalText, evt.runId)`.
- **Evidence after fix:** Terminal output from the real macOS install:

```text
$ ssh nao-mac 'export PATH=/Users/naokitange/.nvm/versions/node/v24.15.0/bin:$PATH; openclaw --version; node --version; nl -ba /Users/naokitange/.nvm/versions/node/v24.15.0/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/tui-LVkXuSWn.js | sed -n "2952,2984p"'
OpenClaw 2026.5.22 (a374c3a)
v24.15.0
  2952                if (!evt.message) {
  2953                    maybeRefreshHistoryForRun(evt.runId, { allowLocalWithoutDisplayableFinal: true });
  2954                    chatLog.dropAssistant(evt.runId);
  2963                if (isCommandMessage(evt.message)) {
  2964                    maybeRefreshHistoryForRun(evt.runId);
  2975                const stopReason = evt.message && typeof evt.message === "object" && !Array.isArray(evt.message) ? typeof evt.message.stopReason === "string" ? evt.message.stopReason : "" : "";
  2976                const finalText = streamAssembler.finalize(evt.runId, evt.message, state.showThinking, evt.errorMessage);
  2977                if (finalText === "(no output)" && !isLocalRunId?.(evt.runId)) chatLog.dropAssistant(evt.runId);
  2978                else chatLog.finalizeAssistant(finalText, evt.runId);
  2979                finalizeRun({
```

- **Observed result after fix:** In the real installed bundle, the empty and command final paths still reload history, but the normal displayable final path goes directly from final text assembly to `finalizeAssistant` and `finalizeRun` without an intervening history reload. That removes the stale-history overwrite point observed in the macOS TUI.
- **What was not tested:** No full upstream package release install was tested; verification used the installed macOS OpenClaw package with the equivalent local patch plus the targeted TUI test below.

Before-patch reference from the same installed bundle backup:

```text
$ ssh nao-mac 'nl -ba /Users/naokitange/.nvm/versions/node/v24.15.0/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/tui-LVkXuSWn.js.bak-eliza-20260524-1436 | sed -n "2968,2984p"'
  2974                }
  2975                maybeRefreshHistoryForRun(evt.runId);
  2976                const stopReason = evt.message && typeof evt.message === "object" && !Array.isArray(evt.message) ? typeof evt.message.stopReason === "string" ? evt.message.stopReason : "" : "";
  2977                const finalText = streamAssembler.finalize(evt.runId, evt.message, state.showThinking, evt.errorMessage);
  2978                if (finalText === "(no output)" && !isLocalRunId?.(evt.runId)) chatLog.dropAssistant(evt.runId);
  2979                else chatLog.finalizeAssistant(finalText, evt.runId);
```

